<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="593" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1011.</note>
                        <head>[Memorandum—Translation.]</head>
                        <p>The local authorities of Del Rio have stopped a contraband shipment of 30
                            guns and 19,000 cartridges intended for the Mexican rebels; the embassy
                            of the Republic hastens to bring this to the knowledge of the Department
                            of State, with a request that it be pleased to make such recommendations
                            as it may see fit to prevent the said implements of war from reaching
                            their destination.</p>
                        <closer><dateline rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican
                                    Embassy</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-20"><hi rend="italic">March 20,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>